Source: WHO Outbreak Reports [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2005_06_21/en/index.html>

Cholera in Afghanistan
----------------------
From 25 May to 16 Jun 2005, the Ministry of Health in Afghanistan reported
a total of 3245 cases of acute watery diarrhea in Kabul city. Out of these
777 were admitted to hospital for severe dehydration. _Vibrio cholerae_ has
been laboratory-confirmed in 30 stool samples out of 44.
The World Health Organization is assisting the Ministry of Health to
administer its control measures and has sent cholera kits for case management.
